sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects the use of PowerShell to identify the current logged user.

match_context.values:
@{ScriptBlockText=
        $Action = New-ScheduledTaskAction -Execute "C:\Users\george\AppData\Roaming\Microsoft\Windows\Applications\Runtime Broker.exe"
        $Trigger = New-ScheduledTaskTrigger -AtLogOn
        $Principal = New-ScheduledTaskPrincipal -UserId $env:USERNAME -LogonType Interactive
        $Principal.RunLevel = 1
        $Settings = New-ScheduledTaskSettingsSet -AllowStartIfOnBatteries -DontStopIfGoingOnBatteries -DontStopOnIdleEnd
        Register-ScheduledTask -Action $Action -Trigger $Tr [TRUNCATED]; Path=; ScriptBlockId=e802307f-211d-4bb4-b745-0e9b42776882; MessageTotal=1; EventID=4104; MessageNumber=1}

crowdsourced_ids_results.rule_msg: POLICY-OTHER HTTP request by IPv4 address attempt
crowdsourced_ids_results.rule_raw: alert tcp any any -> any $HTTP_PORTS ( msg:"POLICY-OTHER HTTP request by IPv4 address attempt"; flow:to_server,established; http_header; content:"Host:",fast_pattern,nocase; pcre:"/^Host\x3a\s*(?:(?:25[0-5]|2[0-4][0-9]|[01]?[0-9]?[0-9])\.){3}(?:25[0-5]|2[0-4][0-9]|[01]?[0-9]?[0-9])\s*:?\s*\d*\s*$/ims"; service:http; reference:url,www.w3.org/Protocols/rfc2616/rfc2616-sec15.html; classtype:policy-violation; sid:50447; rev:1; )
